ce from src/core/types.ts**\n\nThe Plugin system is built on TypeScript interfaces:\n\n```typescript\nexport interface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;              // raw content (markdown or html)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // output path -> rendered content\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n\nexport interface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n\nexport interface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];    // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n\nexport interface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n**Key Points:**\n- Plugins use a hook-based system with three phases: `beforeBuild`, `transformContent`, and `afterBuild`\n- Each hook can be async or sync\n- Plugins have explicit dependencies (creates a DAG - Directed Acyclic Graph)\n- `BuildContext` provides shared state via `data` Map\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Build Engine in src/core/engine.ts**\n\n**Core Responsibilities:**\n\nThe `BuildEngine` class manages:\n\n1. **Plugin Registration** - `registerPlugin()` adds plugins to the engine\n2. **Template Registration** - `registerTemplate()` stores templates by name\n3. **Topological Sort** - `resolvePluginOrder()`:\n   - Uses depth-first search to resolve plugin dependencies\n   - Detects circular dependencies\n   - Detects missing dependencies\n   - Returns plugins in execution order\n\n4. **Build Process** - `build(files: ContentFile[])` executes:\n   - Creates `BuildContext` with config, files, output, assets, and data maps\n   - Resolves plugin execution order\n   - **Phase 1:** Calls `beforeBuild` hooks in order\n   - **Phase 2:** Applies `transformContent` hooks to each file in plugin order\n   - **Phase 3:** Renders files using registered templates\n   - **Phase 4:** Calls `afterBuild` hooks in order\n   - Returns complete `BuildContext`\n\n**Template Rendering Logic:**\n```\nFor each file:\n  - Get template (defaults to \"default\")\n  - If template exists: render with template using file data\n  - If no template: output raw content as is\n  - Output saved to ctx.output with key: `${slug}.html`\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **All Existing Tests in tests/core.test.ts**\n\n**15 Core Tests** (all must pass):\n\n1. **Plugin Registration** - `registers plugins` - Verify plugins can be registered\n2. **Template Registration** - `registers templates` - Verify templates can be registered\n3. **Default Template Rendering** - `builds with default template and renders HTML` - Full HTML page with metadata\n4. **List Template Rendering** - `builds with list template and renders list HTML` - Different template structure\n5. **Raw Output** - `outputs raw content when no matching template` - Falls back to raw content\n6. **Plugin Hooks - beforeBuild** - `calls plugin beforeBuild hook` - Hook is invoked\n7. **Plugin Hooks - transformContent** - `calls plugin transformContent hook to transform files` - Can modify content\n8. **Plugin Hooks - afterBuild** - `calls plugin afterBuild hook` - Hook is invoked\n9. **Dependency Resolution** - `executes plugins in dependency order` - Topological sort works\n10. **Circular Dependency Detection** - `throws on circular dependency` - Error thrown\n11. **Missing Dependency Detection** - `throws on missing dependency` - Error thrown\n12. **Multiple Plugin Transformations** - `applies multiple plugins transformContent in order` - Sequential transformations work\n13. **Shared Data Store** - `provides shared data store in build context` - data Map is accessible\n14. **Metadata Preservation** - `retains file metadata through build` - metadata, date, tags preserved\n15. **Empty File List** - `produces empty output for empty file list` - Handles edge case\n\n---\n\n### 5. **All Plugin Test Files in tests/plugins/**\n\n#### **asset-pipeline.test.ts** (7 tests)\nTests for `createAssetPipelinePlugin()`:\n- Rewrites relative `src=\"./image.png\"` → `src=\"/assets/image.png\"`\n- Rewrites relative `href=\"./doc.pdf\"` → `href=\"/assets/doc.pdf\"`\n- Leaves absolute URLs (https://) unchanged\n- Generates `asset-manifest` in `ctx.data` with list of assets\n- Handles files with no assets\n- Handles multiple assets in one file\n- Accumulates assets across files\n- Does not double-process already-rewritten URLs\n- **Stores:** `ctx.data.set('asset-manifest', { assets: [...] })`\n\n#### **dev-server.test.ts** (7 tests)\nTests for `createDevServerPlugin()`:\n- Stores `dev-server-config` in `ctx.data` (afterBuild hook)\n- Config includes `port` number (default 3000)\n- Config includes `assetPaths` array from `asset-manifest`\n- Config includes `routes` array with handler types: 'asset', 'static'\n- Config includes `searchIndexPath` (looks for `search-index.json` in output)\n- Generates routes for each HTML file in output\n- Handles missing asset-pipeline data gracefully\n- **Stores:** `ctx.data.set('dev-server-config', { port, routes, assetPaths, searchIndexPath })`\n\n#### **markdown-ext.test.ts** (8 tests)\nTests for `createMarkdownExtPlugin()`:\n- Converts markdown to HTML: `# Hello` → `<h1>Hello</h1>`\n- Converts bold: `**bold**` → `<strong>bold</strong>`\n- Handles footnotes with `[^1]` syntax → `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>`\n- Renders footnote section at bottom: `<section class=\"footnotes\">`\n- Converts container syntax `:::note ... :::` → `<div class=\"admonition admonition-note\">`\n- Converts `::: warning` and `::: tip` similarly\n- Preserves existing HTML in content\n- Handles empty content gracefully\n\n#### **rss-feed.test.ts** (9 tests)\nTests for `createRssFeedPlugin()`:\n- Generates `feed.xml` in `ctx.output` (afterBuild hook)\n- Valid RSS 2.0 structure: `<?xml version=\"1.0\"...><rss version=\"2.0\">...<channel>...<item>...</rss>`\n- Feed items contain HTML content wrapped in CDATA: `<![CDATA[...]]>`\n- Includes category tags from files' `tags` array\n- Channel title from `config.title`\n- Items sorted by date (newest first)\n- Handles files without dates (no \"undefined\" pubDate)\n- Uses `baseUrl` for all links\n- Reads `taxonomy-tags` from `ctx.data` for categories\n- **Outputs:** `ctx.output.set('feed.xml', rssXml)`\n\n#### **search-index.test.ts** (8 tests)\nTests for `createSearchIndexPlugin()`:\n- Generates `search-index.json` in `ctx.output` (afterBuild hook)\n- Index entries are array of objects: `{ slug, title, content, tags }`\n- HTML tags stripped from indexed content\n- Includes code block text (from `<code>` tags)\n- Handles empty file list (returns `[]`)\n- Output is valid JSON array\n- Includes `tags` field if present\n- Entries have: `slug`, `title`, `content` (plain text)\n- **Outputs:** `ctx.output.set('search-index.json', JSON.stringify([...]))`\n\n#### **sitemap.test.ts** (8 tests)\nTests for `createSitemapPlugin()`:\n- Generates `sitemap.xml` in `ctx.output` (afterBuild hook)\n- Includes all content page URLs from `ctx.output` (*.html files)\n- Includes tag page URLs from `ctx.output` (tags/*.html)\n- Includes `feed.xml` if present in output\n- URLs built from `config.baseUrl` + path\n- Valid XML structure: `<?xml version=\"1.0\"...><urlset>...<url><loc>...</loc></url>...</urlset>`\n- Handles site with no tag pages gracefully\n- **Outputs:** `ctx.output.set('sitemap.xml', sitemapXml)`\n\n#### **syntax-highlight.test.ts** (8 tests)\nTests for `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin()`:\n- Adds `highlighted` class to code blocks with language: `class=\"language-javascript highlighted\"`\n- Adds `data-language` attribute to `<pre>` tags: `data-language=\"javascript\"`\n- Handles multiple code blocks in one file\n- Does NOT modify blocks without language (no `highlighted` class)\n- Does add classes and attributes to empty code blocks (with language specified)\n- Preserves code block content exactly\n- Does NOT modify inline `<code>` elements (only `<pre><code>` blocks)\n\n#### **taxonomy.test.ts** (8 tests)\nTests for `createTaxonomyPlugin()`:\n- Builds tag index in `beforeBuild` hook: `ctx.data.set('taxonomy-tags', Map<string, ContentFile[]>)`\n- Generates tag listing pages in `afterBuild` hook\n- Tag pages stored as `tags/tagname.html` in `ctx.output`\n- Handles files with no tags\n- Handles multiple tags per file\n- Tag pages list all files with that tag\n- Tag names normalized to lowercase (case-insensitive grouping)\n- Handles empty file list\n- **Stores:** `ctx.data.set('taxonomy-tags', tagMap)` where tagMap is `Map<string, ContentFile[]>`\n\n---\n\n### 6. **package.json Dependencies & Scripts**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-ssg-toolkit\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"SSG Toolkit benchmark - static site generator with DAG plugin system\",\n  \"main\": \"dist/core/index.js\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",              // Compile TypeScript to dist/\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\", // Check code quality\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"          // Run all tests\n  },\n  \n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.18.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.18.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.57.1\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.9.3\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.1.9\"\n  },\n  \n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@types/express\": \"^5.0.6\",\n    \"@types/marked\": \"^5.0.2\",\n    \"express\": \"^5.2.1\",\n    \"marked\": \"^17.0.2\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Available Scripts:**\n- `npm run build` - Compile TypeScript\n- `npm run lint` - ESLint check\n- `npm test` - Vitest (all 75 tests: 15 core + 60 plugin tests)\n\n---\n\n### 7. **tsconfig.json Configuration**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"strict\": true,               // Strict type checking enabled\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",           // Output ES2022\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",           // Node16 module system\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",           // Output directory\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",           // Source root\n    \"declaration\": true,          // Generate .d.ts files\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,      // CommonJS interop\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true          // Skip type checking of declaration files\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*\"]\n}\n```\n\n**Output:** Compiles to `/workspace/dist/` with declarations\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Existing Plugins & Examples**\n\n**Status:** No plugins implemented yet - the `/workspace/src/plugins/` directory only contains `.gitkeep`.\n\n**All 8 plugins must be implemented:**\n\n| Plugin | Hook | Dependencies | Key Features |\n|--------|------|--------------|--------------|\n| **markdown-ext** | transformContent | none | Markdown→HTML, footnotes, admonitions |\n| **asset-pipeline** | transformContent | none | Rewrite asset URLs, generate manifest |\n| **syntax-highlight** | transformContent | none | Language classes on code blocks |\n| **taxonomy** | beforeBuild, afterBuild | none | Tag indexing, tag page generation |\n| **rss-feed** | afterBuild | markdown-ext, taxonomy | RSS 2.0 XML feed generation |\n| **search-index** | afterBuild | markdown-ext, syntax-highlight | JSON search index generation |\n| **sitemap** | afterBuild | taxonomy, rss-feed | XML sitemap generation |\n| **dev-server** | afterBuild | asset-pipeline, search-index | Dev server config generation |\n\n**Wave Dependencies:**\n- **Wave 1 (no deps):** markdown-ext, asset-pipeline, syntax-highlight, taxonomy\n- **Wave 2 (depends on Wave 1):** rss-feed, search-index\n- **Wave 3 (depends on Wave 2):** sitemap, dev-server\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Templates (src/core/templates.ts)**\n\nTwo built-in templates:\n\n**Default Template:**\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <title>${title} | ${siteTitle}</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <article>\n    <h1>${title}</h1>\n    ${date ? `<time>${date}</time>` : ''}\n    <div class=\"content\">${content}</div>\n  </article>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\n**List Template:**\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <title>${title} | ${siteTitle}</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>${title}</h1>\n  <div class=\"list\">${content}</div>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Test Configuration (vitest.config.ts)**\n\n```typescript\nexport default defineConfig({\n  test: {\n    globals: true,           // Use global test APIs\n    testTimeout: 10000,      // 10 second timeout\n  },\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### 11. **ESLint Configuration (.eslintrc.cjs)**\n\n- Parser: TypeScript ESLint parser\n- Extends: eslint:recommended + TypeScript recommended rules\n- Unused variables allowed with `_` prefix\n- Node.js + ES2022 environment\n\n---\n\n### 12. **Key Architecture Insights**\n\n**Plugin Execution Model:**\n1. Plugins execute in topological order (dependencies first)\n2. Each plugin can access and modify `BuildContext`\n3. `ctx.data` is shared state across plugins\n4. `ctx.output` collects generated files\n5. `ctx.files` can be transformed by `transformContent` hooks\n\n**Plugin Patterns:**\n- **Data Storage:** Plugins store results in `ctx.data` Map (e.g., `taxonomy-tags`, `asset-manifest`)\n- **File Generation:** Plugins generate files in `ctx.output` Map\n- **Content Transformation:** Plugins modify individual `ContentFile` objects\n- **Sequential:** Plugin hooks run in dependency order\n- **Hook-based:** Three lifecycle hooks (before/transform/after)\n\n**Data Flow:**\n```\nInput Files → beforeBuild hooks → transformContent hooks (per file) → \nTemplate Rendering → afterBuild hooks → Build Context Output\n```\n\n---\n\nThis is a complete, thoroughly documented SSG toolkit ready for 8-plugin implementation following the test specifications."}],"totalDurationMs":48190,"totalTokens":37646,"totalToolUseCount":21,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":940,"cache_read_input_tokens":32185,"output_tokens":4517,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":940,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[]}}}
